<br>
How do ye warriors make a lot of plat? With the prices of some of the weapons I have been looking at, how can warrior make plat? Some toons make serious plat porting, etc....this isnt sour grapes, but a honest question looking to help a newbie warrior. <br>
<br>
Kelor  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=burumpus>Burumpus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/02 2:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: money</span><hr size=1> sorry man...i've yet to find a sure fire way of making plat as a warrior.  About the only way you are going to make plat as a warrior is to be tha shiznitt at some tradeskill(probably smithing)  warriors are not a class that is born to be rich.  we are poor, hungry, angry, and confused.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=376724">Burumpus 62 NomeWar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://liquid2k.com/durtee/pictures/BurumpusSIg.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tathlyn>Tathlyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/02 2:40 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://webpages.charter.net/tathlyn/magician2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: money</span><hr size=1> Ummm...for the most part you don't.  Just get lucky in random for items you can sell is only way for warriors generally.  <br>
<br>
Only other way is to have alot of spare time and start up plat to max out one of the more useful tradeskills which are generally in regular demand.  Smithing is good for high end cultural. Fletching is relatively constant for high end bows.  Tailoring goes in spurts whenever something new comes out, but then dies out until the next new good thing.  Now that the earring of Solstice has really slowed down in demand, pottery is really only for a make on demand.  Tinkering is mostly done by request, but that is restricted just to gnomes.  Forget Jewlcraft unless you have your own enchanter to do the bars for you, and if you don't mind spending alot of time pretty much just catering to the case by case demand, and pray that you don't just run into people wanting blue diamonds since those are ridiculously high because of the cultural armor demands.  Brewing and Baking while not expensive to make, are very time consuming, and you have to sell tons of the items to build up your plat.<br>
<br>
If you do decide to go the tradeskill route, the most useful place where you can find most of the information or ask on the boards there if not listed in any of the sections is at:<br>
http://www.eqtraders.com <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:Lucida Calligraphy;font-size:small;">Safe journies and good adventures,</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-family:Lucida Calligraphy;font-size:small;"> The Blueberry,<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Tathlyn Sei'Taer<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=149908">62 Warlord</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tathlyn>Tathlyn</A> at: 11/11/02 2:46:50 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hyardgune>Hyardgune</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 141<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/02 2:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: money</span><hr size=1> Make a druid or wizard.  I only play a warrior, my highest level alt is a 20, so I feel the no cash pain.  I have yet to find a good way to make money, I just keep leveling and hope that one day I'll get nice gear on drops.  Honestly, levels = money.  The higher level you are, the better the money making opportunities are.  You can get into places where you can get decent cash drops, gems, items, etc, then you'll make some cash.  Unfortunately, unless you have another character, you are likely to be poor.<br>
<br>
Your other option, once you have a bit of cash, start playing the market, buy items low and sell them high.  Chances are you'll spend a lot of time in the bazaar, which means you aren't levelling... <p>Hyardgune Varangian<br>
60 Ogre Warlord<br>
Solusek Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kelor@thesteelwarrior>kelor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/02 3:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  re: money</span><hr size=1> Thank to all of ye for the replies. I was just curious. Looking on alla's web site I see some of the ridiculous prices that some of the better weapons go for and was wondering how us warriors were supposed to afford them...I saw several weapons going for 7-10,000 PP and Im thinking I wont ever see 2000 PP much less 10,000. I guess Lamentation and FBSS and other high end stuff will be out of my hands.....such is our life. Thanks to ye for listening. <br>
<br>
Kelor  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skankfu>Skankfu</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/02 3:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: re: money</span><hr size=1> those arent really high end<br>
teehee <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=keaneabrams>Keane Abrams</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/02 10:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: re: money</span><hr size=1> The best advice I can give for a warrior main with no alt over 20 is to just level and try and get in some decent loot camps. Eventually you will win the roll on a nice item that you will sell for decent loot. And you can always spend a thousand hours in Rathe mnts grouped with a healer and make some cash that way.<br>
<br>
Good luck. <p>Keane Abrams<br>
60 Warlord<br>
Tunare's Benevolence<br>
Zebuxoruk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=spinetwist>Spinetwist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.joydrop.net/spine/spineicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/12/02 10:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: re: money</span><hr size=1> I addressed this in my War guide because I too was very frustrated at the lack of funds I had available to me in my early barshin days. Well I can honestly say it all boils down to level. I was told over and over again to be patient and loot will come with higher levels which means more money. At level 60 I can generally agree that getting money is not very hard and many places such as Velks, or Sebs offer the most opportunity for gems which you sell for pp. Pre 55 I made the most money collecting Fine Steel Weapons from Chardok, selling things I won in Chardok, and also farming the Hill Giants in Rathe Mountains. My record drop in Rathe Mountains was a giant who dropped 48pp and an FS weapon and some lame gem. This is pretty pathetic to some ppl but damn what else can we wars do? <br>
<br>
For me, I managed to save 65k for a CoCW in a few weeks in Sebs. Stick to the high gem camps. <br>
<br>
LIke most of the guys here said, with your level its tough to generate cash so I would concentrate on level and worry about the $$ later since it will fall into play. Dont sweat it. <br>
<br>
-Spine- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kiyallmanebloodcry>KiyallmaneBloodcry</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 314<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/13/02 1:46 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~bass72/_uimages/1C.gif hieght=140 width=113></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: re: money</span><hr size=1> /blinks<br>
